review_blob: Appealing brown color and nutty,toasty smell and taste. Goes down smooth. Great on tap.
I usually get this beer whenever I go to Heartland - it has a great mouth-feel and slides down very easily. And it is always nice and fresh!
I like Original Coors - dont call it regular Coors - the Coors people dont like that - but an easy drinking beer with a decent clear flavor.
Drink only in emergency (ie - only beer left)- it really has no taste - good or bad
A friend of mine dubbed this beer liquid crack at a beer festival in Brooklyn once. He wasnt far off IMO.
I wanted something light so I tried soemthing old but new in my neighborhood and was pleasantly surprised. Nice flavor & finish veryeasy to drink and enjoy. A bit similar to Origial Coors.
Not as consistantly good as Guinness is on tap - is that due to Guinness diligence or Murphys lack of? When good it is a fine beer.
One of my favorites - just tried the new draft bottle and it was quite good. Nothing beats a well poured draft though.
